<subSubSection pageId="198" pageNumber="199" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Omus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Omus</taxonomicName>
Eschscholtz, 1829: 3. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eschscholtz" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Omus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="californicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Omus californicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Eschscholtz, 1829 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">omos</emphasis>
(cruel), possibly alluding to the apparent ferocious habits of the species in the eyes of Eschscholtz [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="198" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Leptomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Leptomus</taxonomicName>
Casey, 1914: 1. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Omus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="198" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="198" pageNumber="199">Omus submetallicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
